Subject: [PATCH] ASoC: soc-dai.c: add .no_capture_mute support
Git-commit: 350d993510115e3d9e78f1b3359bff7b68e88418
Patch-mainline: v5.9-rc1
References: jsc#SLE-16518

snd_soc_dai_digital_mute() is internally using both
mute_stream() (1) or digital_mute() (2), but the difference between
these 2 are only handling "direction".
We can merge digital_mute() into mute_stream

	int snd_soc_dai_digital_mute(xxx, int direction)
	{
		...
		else if (dai->driver->ops->mute_stream)
(1)			return dai->driver->ops->mute_stream(xxx, direction);
		else if (direction == SNDRV_PCM_STREAM_PLAYBACK &&
			 dai->driver->ops->digital_mute)
(2)			return dai->driver->ops->digital_mute(xxx);
		...
	}

To prepare merging mute_stream()/digital_mute(),
this patch adds .no_capture_mute support to emulate .digital_mute().

